description: On Disk Monthly #88 What's On This Issue Medieval Conquest This Windows game is a derivative of Chess but it should be fun even for non-chess players. Pieces move the same as in chess, but pieces have strengths and weaknesses that force a major change in strategy. Besides normal attacks, Medieval Conquest adds the ability to cast spells. Bubba's Cavernous Conundrum Some of our most popular items from the early days of "Big Blue Disk" were the continuing adventures of "Alfredo." The Alfredo adventures were simple animated "movies" that the user sat back and watched as Alfredo suffered a series of misadventures. Bubba's adventures are similar, with two major exceptions. Bubba's graphics are as good as most commercial games, and the user actually controls Bubba's actions. Crypto Sleuth Here is another series of cryptograms to solve, using our popular cryptogram program "Crypto Sleuth." We have dug deep into our quotation library for these puzzles. Have fun! Memo Writer One of the most popular items that we ever published on ODM was Memo Writer. We have had numerous requests for new templates for the program and we have published two complete sets on previous issues. We have two new templates on this disk ("meetnote.mtp and planner.mtp) and we have a new and improved version of the program PLUS we have included all of the templates from previous issues. Forty Thieves The single most common game request we get is for new solitaire card games. We have heard your requests and here is our response. Forty Thieves is a two-deck solitaire card game that is both challenging and fun. Look for more games like this in the future. Windows TrueType fonts Here are more in our continuing series of TrueType fonts. This month we are going all out and providing you with six different fonts to install. At least one of them ought to strike your fancy! Alison is a decorative font, Downtown is unique, Marking Pen will intrigue you, New Deal (and New Deal Bold) are useful and Niverse will round out your collection. .PCX Graphics This month our art department has generated a new batch of .PCX clip art for your use. Included are dice, cards and other images from your friendly neighborhood casino. Use these in your party invitations, or just to spice up any document.

description: ZZTV is a community project started by Dark FLR in 1998. ZZTers can create and contribute channels, which are small ZZT worlds that can contain any kind of content the author wishes: previews of upcoming games, artwork, minigames, stories, etc... These channels are traditionally given names that begin with the "#" symbol (e.g., "#bakedcheese"). All of the channels are sent to the person in charge of ZZTV; the project leader is then responsible for compiling the contributions into a series of volumes and releasing them to the public. ZZTVs are done at the rate of about one per year. Each ZZTV is numbered; for example, the current ZZTV-in-progress is ZZTV 11. The person in charge of ZZTV changes fairly frequently; Zenith Nadir owned the project between issues 4-7 before passing the mantle on, with the more recent project leaders being MadTom, Commodore, and now bitbot.
subject: ZZT diskmags
